The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, March 9: The board of directors of Bajaj Auto today approved the appointment of Rajiv Bajaj as the new managing director with effect from April 1. The elder son of Rahul Bajaj, who is currently joint managing director, takes over as the new managing director for a period of five years from his father, who will now remain as the chairman of the board. The board cleared a fresh term of five years for Rahul Bajaj as chairman from April 1.

 New Delhi, March 9: The government today said it has set up dedicated Central Bureau of Investigation cells in four metros for detecting and checking telecom related frauds.

 Calcutta, March 9: Bata India Ltd today filed offer document with the Securities and Exchange Board of India for its proposed rights issue. Sources said Bata would offer the issue to its existing shareholders in the proportion of 1:4.

 Calcutta, March 9: Titagarh Industries (TIL) would restructure itself by demerging its paper business. It will hive off the two mills located at Kankinara and Titagarh into separate companies.

 New Delhi, March 9: Telecom tribunal TDSAT today dismissed Bharti?s petition for a refund of Rs 135 crore paid by it as licence fees for entry into basic services prior to the new uniform licencing regime introduced by the government.




